    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-04-02T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-04-02T19:00:00-05:00" n="62"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d62">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.5/3–3151: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        United States Deputy Representative on the North Atlantic Council</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_SCM1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Spofford</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">at London</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d62fn1">Repeated to Paris and to Frankfurt for Heidelberg.
                        The telegram was drafted by <persName corresp="#p_VLC1">L. C.
                            Vass</persName> (<gloss target="#t_RA1">RA</gloss>) and cleared by him
                        with <persName corresp="#p_MEM1">Martin</persName>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_RGH1">Raynor</persName> (<gloss target="#t_BNA1"
                        >BNA</gloss>), and, in substance, with <persName corresp="#p_CH1"
                            >Cleveland</persName> (<gloss target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss>).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-04-02T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 2, 1951—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Todep1">Todep</gloss> 342. For <persName corresp="#p_SCM1"
                        >Spofford</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_KM1">Katz</persName>.</p>
                <pb facs="0149" n="111" xml:id="pg_111"/>
                <p>1. Highly gratified at success your efforts persuade UK accept <gloss
                        target="#t_FEB1">FEB</gloss> resolution, <gloss target="#t_Depto1"
                        >Depto</gloss> 699, Mar 31.<note n="2" xml:id="d62fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> This is State <gloss target="#t_ECA1"
                        >ECA</gloss> message.</p>
                <p>2. However, are concerned, as sure you are, at report UK thinking of designating
                        <persName corresp="#p_RE2">Roll</persName>, which clear evidence UK does not
                    share our view that <gloss target="#t_FEB1">FEB</gloss> major body warranting
                    reps at sub-ministerial level. US does not see <gloss target="#t_FEB1"
                        >FEB</gloss> as simply <gloss target="#t_WG1">WG</gloss> 12 under different
                    name but as <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> body with important functions
                    in number other fields calling for reps of stature <persName corresp="#p_HPEL1"
                        >Hall-Patch</persName> and in our case <persName corresp="#p_WCT1">Tyler
                        Wood</persName>.</p>
                <p>3. In our view relative status of <persName corresp="#p_HPEL1"
                        >Hall-Patch</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_HM1"
                        >Hoyer-Millar</persName> in UK shld not be insuperable obstacle in naming
                    former.</p>
                <p>4. Leave to your discretion what if any informal approaches to Brits you may wish
                    to make to convey our general reaction. Wld consider most unfortunate firm UK
                    position appoint <persName corresp="#p_RE2">Roll</persName> before organizing
                    comite spells out functions which we convinced will show need for highest level
                    reps.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_ADG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
